\chapter{Introduction} \label{sec:intro}

This is a general introduction to what the thesis is all about -- it is
not just a description of the contents of each section. Include in this chapter all fundamental concepts that are relevant to the understanding of your problem. Once all such concepts have been addressed, briefly summarize the question (you will be stating the question in detail later), some of
the reasons why it is a worthwhile question, and perhaps give an overview
of your main results. This is a birds-eye view of the answers to the main
questions answered in the thesis.

